<header class="hero" style="padding-bottom: 4rem;">
  <span class="eyebrow">Fundamentals</span>
  <h1>What is a Charter Airline?</h1>
  <p>The basics of the charter airline business model — how it works, why it works, who flies on it, and how it compares to a traditional scheduled airline.</p>
</header>

<main class="wrap">

  <div class="section-label">Definition</div>
  <h2 class="title">A different way to fly</h2>
  <div class="definition-box">
    A <strong>charter airline</strong> is a type of airline that operates flights on a <strong>non-scheduled, on-demand basis</strong>, as opposed to flying fixed routes at published times like a conventional airline. Instead of selling individual seats on a regular timetable, charter airlines fly when there's demand &mdash; often for holiday packages, tour operators, sports teams, or corporate groups.
  </div>

  <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:3rem;">How it Works</div>
  <h2 class="title">The charter model</h2>
  <div class="grid cols-2">
    <div class="card">
      <h3><span class="icon-badge">&#128269;</span> Package holidays, not loose tickets</h3>
      <p>Customers purchase a complete holiday &mdash; flights, hotel, transfers &mdash; rather than booking separate travel services individually.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3><span class="icon-badge">&#127797;</span> Leisure-first focus</h3>
      <p>Charter airlines operate mainly for leisure travelers flying to holiday destinations, rather than serving business commuter routes.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:3rem;">Why it Works</div>
  <h2 class="title">Why the model is so effective</h2>
  <div class="grid cols-3">
    <div class="card">
      <h3><span class="icon-badge">&#128279;</span> Vertical Integration</h3>
      <p>A charter airline's parent group can control flights, hotels, cruises, and excursions all under one roof.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3><span class="icon-badge">&#127757;</span> Direct Holiday Destinations</h3>
      <p>Charter networks often serve 80+ leisure destinations worldwide, flying customers straight to where they're going.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3><span class="icon-badge">&#128274;</span> One-Stop Booking</h3>
      <p>Flight, hotel, and transport can all be booked under a single reservation &mdash; simple for the customer, profitable for the company.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:3rem;">Who Flies Charter</div>
  <h2 class="title">Customers of charter airlines</h2>
  <p class="lead">Charter airlines serve a much wider range of clients than just holidaymakers.</p>
  <div class="grid cols-5">
    <div class="card" style="text-align:center;"><div class="icon-badge" style="margin:0 auto 0.6rem;">&#128181;</div><h3 style="justify-content:center;">Tour Operators</h3></div>
    <div class="card" style="text-align:center;"><div class="icon-badge" style="margin:0 auto 0.6rem;">&#127970;</div><h3 style="justify-content:center;">Corporations</h3></div>
    <div class="card" style="text-align:center;"><div class="icon-badge" style="margin:0 auto 0.6rem;">&#9917;</div><h3 style="justify-content:center;">Sports Teams</h3></div>
    <div class="card" style="text-align:center;"><div class="icon-badge" style="margin:0 auto 0.6rem;">&#127963;</div><h3 style="justify-content:center;">Governments</h3></div>
    <div class="card" style="text-align:center;"><div class="icon-badge" style="margin:0 auto 0.6rem;">&#128230;</div><h3 style="justify-content:center;">Cargo Clients</h3></div>
  </div>

  <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:3rem;">Key Characteristics</div>
  <h2 class="title">Three defining traits</h2>
  <div class="timeline">
    <div class="timeline-step">
      <div class="dot">&#10003;</div>
      <h4>On-demand operation</h4>
      <p>Flights operate on demand rather than on a fixed published schedule.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-step">
      <div class="dot">&#10003;</div>
      <h4>Bulk purchasing</h4>
      <p>Customers pay for the whole aircraft, or tour operators purchase large blocks of seats.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-step">
      <div class="dot">&#10003;</div>
      <h4>Contract-based revenue</h4>
      <p>Revenue comes from charter contracts rather than regular individual ticket sales.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:3rem;">Operations</div>
  <h2 class="title">How charter flights operate</h2>
  <div class="grid cols-3">
    <div class="card">
      <h3><span class="icon-badge">&#9992;&#65039;</span> Demand-driven flights</h3>
      <p>Flights operate when demand exists, rather than running every day regardless of how full the plane is.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3><span class="icon-badge">&#128197;</span> Seasonal routes</h3>
      <p>Routes can change seasonally &mdash; more flights to sun destinations in summer, ski resorts in winter, for example.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3><span class="icon-badge">&#128205;</span> Direct &amp; remote access</h3>
      <p>Charter airlines often fly directly to holiday destinations or remote locations that scheduled airlines don't serve.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:3rem;">Revenue Sources</div>
  <h2 class="title">Where the money comes from</h2>
  <div class="grid cols-4">
    <div class="card"><h3><span class="icon-badge">&#9992;&#65039;</span> Aircraft charter fees</h3></div>
    <div class="card"><h3><span class="icon-badge">&#127757;</span> Package holiday contracts</h3></div>
    <div class="card"><h3><span class="icon-badge">&#128230;</span> Cargo charter services</h3></div>
    <div class="card"><h3><span class="icon-badge">&#127960;</span> Corporate &amp; VIP transport</h3></div>
  </div>

  <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:3rem;">Comparison</div>
  <h2 class="title">Charter vs. scheduled airlines</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Charter Airline</th><th>Scheduled Airline</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Flight schedule</td><td class="highlight">On demand / seasonal</td><td>Fixed timetable</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Booking method</td><td class="highlight">Packages or whole plane</td><td>Individual tickets</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Pricing</td><td class="highlight">Contract or package price</td><td>Seat fares change</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Route network</td><td class="highlight">Holiday / special places</td><td>Regular city routes</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Flexibility</td><td class="highlight">Can adjust</td><td>Less flexible</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

</main>

