<header class="hero" style="padding-bottom: 4rem;">
  <span class="eyebrow">Case Study &middot; Team 5</span>
  <h1>TUI Airways</h1>
  <p>Europe's leading charter airline, and a core part of the world's largest integrated tourism group.</p>
</header>

<main class="wrap">

  <div class="section-label">Company Profile</div>
  <h2 class="title">Introduction to TUI Airways</h2>
  <div class="two-col">
    <div>
      <div class="grid cols-2">
        <div class="card"><h3><span class="icon-badge">&#127983;&#65039;</span> Founded</h3><p>1962, London, United Kingdom</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3><span class="icon-badge">&#127968;</span> Headquarters</h3><p>Luton, Bedfordshire, England</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3><span class="icon-badge">&#127757;</span> Destinations</h3><p>100+ destinations worldwide</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3><span class="icon-badge">&#9992;&#65039;</span> Fleet</h3><p>Boeing 737-800, Boeing 737 MAX 8, Boeing 787 Dreamliner</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="definition-box">
      TUI Airways is a <strong>charter airline</strong> and part of the <strong>TUI Group</strong> &mdash; one of the world's largest integrated tourism businesses. Rather than operating as a standalone airline, it functions as the flight arm of a much larger holiday ecosystem.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:3rem;">Group Structure</div>
  <h2 class="title">TUI Group: an integrated tourism ecosystem</h2>
  <p class="lead">TUI Airways is one piece of a much larger group that controls almost every part of a customer's holiday.</p>
  <div class="org-chart">
    <div class="org-root">TUI GROUP</div>
    <div class="org-children">
      <div class="org-child"><span class="emoji">&#9992;&#65039;</span><span class="name">Airlines</span></div>
      <div class="org-child"><span class="emoji">&#127976;</span><span class="name">Hotels</span></div>
      <div class="org-child"><span class="emoji">&#128674;</span><span class="name">Cruises</span></div>
      <div class="org-child"><span class="emoji">&#127965;&#65039;</span><span class="name">Excursions</span></div>
      <div class="org-child"><span class="emoji">&#128218;</span><span class="name">Travel Agencies</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="lead" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">The Airlines branch flows into <strong>Holiday Flights</strong>, which serve <strong>Leisure Travelers</strong> &mdash; tying the airline directly into TUI's broader holiday business.</p>

  <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:3rem;">Network</div>
  <h2 class="title">Why TUI uses multiple hubs</h2>
  <p class="lead">Unlike many traditional airlines that rely on a single dominant hub, TUI Airways operates a <strong>multi-hub model</strong> &mdash; bringing holiday flights closer to customers across the UK.</p>

  <div class="two-col">
    <div>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.8rem;">Primary Hubs</h3>
      <div class="hub-list">
        <div class="hub-pill">London Gatwick (LGW)</div>
        <div class="hub-pill">Manchester (MAN)</div>
        <div class="hub-pill">Birmingham (BHX)</div>
      </div>
      <h3 style="margin:1.5rem 0 0.8rem;">Major Operating Bases</h3>
      <div class="hub-list">
        <div class="hub-pill">London Luton (LTN)</div>
        <div class="hub-pill">Bristol (BRS)</div>
        <div class="hub-pill">Newcastle (NCL)</div>
        <div class="hub-pill">East Midlands (EMA)</div>
        <div class="hub-pill">Glasgow (GLA)</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>&#10003; Key Benefit</h3>
      <p>A multi-hub network brings holiday flights closer to customers across the UK, reducing travel time to the airport and widening TUI's reach into regional markets.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:3rem;">Network Strategy</div>
  <h2 class="title">Multi-hub vs. traditional hub</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Traditional Airline</th><th>TUI Airways</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>One dominant hub</td><td class="highlight">Multiple hubs</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Connecting passengers</td><td class="highlight">Direct holiday flights</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Business + leisure focus</td><td class="highlight">Leisure-focused</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Hub-and-spoke network</td><td class="highlight">Point-to-point network</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:3rem;">Airport Relationships</div>
  <h2 class="title">Airport ownership structure</h2>
  <p class="lead">TUI does not own any of the airports it flies from &mdash; it forms long-term commercial partnerships with airport operators of all ownership types.</p>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Airport</th><th>Ownership Type</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>London Gatwick (LGW)</td><td class="highlight">Private Ownership</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Manchester (MAN)</td><td class="highlight">Public-Private Partnership</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Birmingham (BHX)</td><td class="highlight">Local Authority Ownership</td></tr>
        <tr><td>London Luton (LTN)</td><td class="highlight">Council-Owned, Privately Managed</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:3rem;">Partnership</div>
  <h2 class="title">The TUI &ndash; Airport relationship</h2>
  <div class="grid cols-2">
    <div class="card">
      <h3><span class="icon-badge">&#9992;&#65039;</span> TUI provides</h3>
      <p>Passenger traffic, tourism growth, year-round operations, and commercial revenue to its partner airports.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3><span class="icon-badge">&#127976;</span> Airports provide</h3>
      <p>Gates &amp; terminals, take-off/landing slots, ground handling support, and marketing partnerships in return.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:3rem;">Outcome</div>
  <h2 class="title">How airport ownership affects TUI</h2>
  <div class="pros-cons">
    <div class="pc-block good">
      <h4>&#10003; Advantages</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>No airport ownership costs</li>
        <li>Flexible allocation of aircraft</li>
        <li>Easy expansion into regional markets</li>
        <li>Lower financial risk</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="pc-block bad">
      <h4>&#9888; Challenges</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Airport charges and fees</li>
        <li>Slot availability constraints</li>
        <li>Dependence on airport operational performance</li>
        <li>Limited control over infrastructure decisions</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="definition-box" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
    <strong>Bottom line:</strong> flexibility is the biggest advantage of TUI's airport-partner model &mdash; but TUI remains dependent on each airport's own operational factors.
  </div>

</main>

